task.summary: some clean-up and more edge weighting schemes
stub for the ordering of modules during folding

some cleanup in CSV-generation
- moved to only 2 routines - one to generate csv with focus on amino acids - one to generate csv with focus on interactions - about to move everything else (i.e. selection/filtering/folding) to R
routine for contact tables and coupling csv
extends contact csv generation by number of observations

support for crude PDB format flaws found in CASP
- equant reimpl stub - support for sscore as target function - drops element parsing in StructureParser and infers it rather from pdbName of group
stub for contacts-module and cone-peeling algorithm

parametrization of reconstruction pipeline
- adaptation for start2fold dataset
clean-up and recreation of results as constraints were swapped

dedicated module for start2fold
- major clean-up - dataset creation somewhat streamlined - manual efforts remain - mapping of early folding residues corrected via dedicated sequence alignment - PyMol visualization script for distribution of early folding residues
option to skip hetatms during parsing
creation of GMLVQ dataset once again

toward statistics files
- equant parser - PyMOL generation of functional residue rendering - support for native Fisher's test though best avoided and done by R

tweaks on topological descriptors
betweenness still bugged
improvements to generation of EFR-GMLVQ arffs
finalizes EFR feature computation and CSV generation
logging levels reduced for PLIP parsing
generation and reconstruction performance csv and cleanup
EFR visualization of prediction on aaRS
